      • create

        public java.lang.String create()
        Creating template {"timestamp":"timestamp_value"}, where timestamp_value- timestamp value from tmlStr. Example: 
         
 String tml = new TmlTimestampJson(new TmlTimestamp()).create();
 // This code creating template:
 // {"timestamp":"2022-02-24T00:38:13.573"}
        If tmlStr does not match pattern, then method return {"timestamp":null}.
